Patch Set 10:

(1 comment)

The python path isn't known to the running python code because of what is mentioned in the commit message. You could attempt to figure it out by investigating $PATH etc. Except that would not be a guarantee on all environments and more likely to get things wrong. Trying to be more clever here is more effort than it's worth. '/usr/bin/python*' is just a default, and frankly one that will likely work for the majority of users. If it doesn't you just set it to what your environment demands.

Patch Set 11:

We're going to hold off on this until rocky-1 after we've had a chance to talk at the PTG.  I'm in agreement with the general strategy on this patch.  The sticking point is that the Glance community at the 15 Feb meeting feels that merging this may give the wrong impression about the current state of Glance uwsgi support.  This is a key patch to get one of the Glance tasks to work correctly under uwsgi, but currently Glance tasks don't run under uwsgi.
